We need to find the value of the sum \( x_{2019} + 2x_{2020} + 4x_{2021} + 8x_{2022} \). First, we recognize that \( 7S_n \equiv 1 \pmod{2^n} \) implies \( S_n \) is the modular inverse of 7 modulo \( 2^n \). The sequence \( S_n \) must therefore be such that each prefix forms the inverse of 7 modulo increasing powers of 2. By examining the pattern of the inverses of 7 modulo \( 2^n \), we observe that the sequence of bits \( x_k \) repeats every 4 terms.
